Changes in scope, such as the segment, are handled at the regulator level. Within RCM, members of Enterprise Compliance are responsible for making these changes. Adding or removing a segment is considered a material change and will require the section's mappings to be confirmed again. However, as before, only one person from any relevant segment needs to provide confirmation.

2. It is not feasible to monitor the specific content of a section in RCM because it consists of free-form text, and doing so would cause a lot of unnecessary noise, such as changes in spacing or grammar to an entire RegBook.
